Bachelor's Thesis: Passenger Flow Analysis using Computer Vision
================================================================

How To Build
-------------

	cd bachelor_thesis
	make
	make link

Executable binary is located in bin/, object files are located in obj/

Project Structure
-----------------
	main:	Entry point for the core application
	cvutil:	OpenCV library wrapper
	debug:	Plays the role like Android Log.d()
	vibe:	Foreground segmenter

General Architecture
--------------------
		----------------
		|Frame Sequence|
		----------------
			|
			v
		---------------
		|Current Frame|
		---------------
			|
			v	 -------------------------
			-------->|Update Background Model|
			|	 -------------------------
			|		|
			v		|
		---------------------	|
		|Foreground (binary)|<---
		---------------------
			|
			v
		-----------------
		|Contours	|
		-----------------
			|             -----------
			|<------------|Extractor|
			|             -----------
			v
		---------------------
		|Blobs of Interested|
		---------------------
			|
			|
			v
		-----------------
		|Tracker	|
		-----------------

Extractor
---------

1. Overview

	Input: a refined binary image - cv::Mat
	Output: a vector of  BOI (Blobs of Interest)

2. How:
	Pick blobs based on criteria:
		+ Minimum Area					[x]
		+ Aspect Ratio (h / w of bounding box)		[x]
		+ Extent (object area / bounding box area)	[?]

	More on: http://docs.opencv.org/3.2.0/d1/d32/tutorial_py_contour_properties.html

